Class Description
CampusBuilding
This represents one immutable entry of data in campus_buildings.csv, including the short and long names for buildings and other locations on campus, and the (x, y) image coordinates of that location.
CampusMap
This class implements and overrides the methods in ModelAPI by taking an existing short name of a building and using it to find a path between buildings.
CampusPath
This represents one immutable entry of the data in campus_paths.csv,
CampusPathsParser
A utility class capable of parsing data in campus buildings and campus paths files in their expected formats.
CampusPathsParser.ParserException
An Exception class representing an error during parsing.
CoordinateProperties
Represents the different possible basis arrangements for a two-dimensional cartesian coordinate space.
DijkstrasPaths
Builds graph from file and finds path between nodes using Dijkstra's algorithm.
Direction
Represents one of the 4 major or 4 minor compass directions, as is capable of resolving the direction between two points or from the origin to a point.
Entry
Entry class to compare list of maps for priority queue Takes value of list/maps and compares
InputHandler
An InputHandler is capable of responding to a String command being input.
ModelAPI
This interface represents the API that the text interface view/controller require models to implement.
Path
This represents an immutable path between two cartesian coordinate points, particularly Path#getStart() and Path#getEnd().
Pathfinder
Pathfinder represents a complete application capable of responding to user prompts to provide a variety of information about campus buildings and paths between them.
Point
Represents an immutable cartesian coordinate point.
TextInterfaceController
This class does most of the controller work for the text user interface version of the pathfinder application.
TextInterfaceView
This is a view that allows interaction with a command-line user through a series of commands.
